            "title": "Shell increases stake in Brazil pre-salt oil projects",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>Shell PLC - London based oil and gas exploration company - Shell Brasil secures additional equity in Brazil's pre-salt oil projects following an auction led by Pre-Sal Petroleo. Together with Petrobras, Shell Brasil deepened its stake in Atapu and Mero units, acquiring just under 27% of Atapu Open acreage and 20% of Mero Open acreage. With this acquisition, Shell Brasil increases its participating interest in the units from 16.6% to 16.9% in Atapu and from 19.3% to 20% in Mero. Both projects are located in the offshore Santos Basin.</p><p></p><p>Current share price: 2,803.50 pence</p><!-- Article --><p>\n12-month change: up 11% </p><p></p><p>By Jeremy Cutler, Alliance News reporter</p><p></p><p>Comments and questions to newsroom@alliancenews.com</p><p></p><p>Copyright 2025 Alliance News Ltd. All Rights Reserved.</p></div>",
